  Today there is much confusion as to where to begin with managing projects. You can choose a standardized method like PMBOK or Prince2. You can choose and Agile method like XP, Scrum, or Kanban. Even within Scrum there is heated discussion as to which type of Scrum is best. 
  <br/><br/>In this provocative talk, Jesse Fewell says none of it matters; no-one wants to admit that very formal method has both its successes and its failures.
